      <hedline>
        <hl1>IF YOU ASK ME</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Composer Osvaldo Golijov says favorite musical performance of 2002 was by Brazilian singer Caetano Veloso in movie Talk to Her; photo (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>OSVALDO GOLIJOV  Composer</p>
        <p>In ''Talk to Her,'' the new Almodóvar movie, which flows like an opera Mozart would have written had he reached 50, the Brazilian singer Caetano Veloso appears on screen and sings ''Cucurrucucú Paloma'' to the astonishment of the on- and off-screen audiences. Caetano's angelic falsetto offers a time-stopping blessing and love lesson that sounds as if imparted by a 211-year-old Papageno, now wise, wistful and infinitely generous.</p>
      </block>
